headline: Franklin Templeton CEO on Tariffs, Fed, US Economy
summary: Franklin Templeton President and CEO Jenny Johnson discussed the "interlocking" issues of tariffs, taxes and deregulation, expecting one interest rate cut this year from the Federal Reserve, the "pretty strong" US economy, and the importance of responsibly adding private assets to the firm's wealth channel. Johnson spoke on the sidelines of The Milken Institute Global Conference in Beverly Hills, California.

headline: Franklin's April AUM Balance Declines Sequentially on Net Outflows
summary: BEN's total AUM declined to $1.53 trillion, impacted by net outflows, though alternative assets reflected modest growth.
